rl=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/largest-collection-of-dinosaur-eggs|website=Guinness World Records|accessdate=5 August 2015|title=Largest collection of dinosaur eggs}}</ref> Dinosaur skeletons and fossilized footprints have also been found nearby.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/11550057/Builders-find-dinosaur-eggs-in-paleontologists-paradise-in-China.html|title=Builders find dinosaur eggs in paleontologist's paradise in China|author=Tom Phillips|work=Daily Telegraph|date=20 April 2015|accessdate=20 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Findings ===\nA dinosaur egg fossil dated back to the Late [[Cretaceous]] was discovered by primary school student named Zhang Yangzhe while playing near the [[Dong River (China)|Dong River]] in 2019 in July. The boy's mother, Li Xiaofang, later contacted the Heyuan Dinosaur Museum members, and under their excavation guidance more than 10 dinosaur egg fossils each about 9 centimeters in diameter and dating back to 66 million years were revealed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/201907/26/WS5d3ac1b9a310d830564013c6.html|title=Boy finds 66-million-year-old dinosaur eggs - Chinadaily.com.cn|last=\u6c5f\u5dcd|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archaeology-world.com/chinese-boy-accidentally-finds-66-million-year-old-dinosaur-eggs/|title=Chinese Boy Accidentally Finds 66-Million-Year-Old Dinosaur Eggs {{!}} ARCHAEOLOGY WORLD|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MjM5MTA4NzgxNA==&mid=2651205545&idx=3&sn=dab82422bb5676931e8575547ff545a9&chksm=bd4862008a3feb1670ccdd575e27787eaa7da66ad56b717cffe35513199379e36c54f888e89d#rd|script-title=zh:\u6cb3\u6e90\u53c8\u73b0\u6050\u9f99\u86cb\u5316\u77f3\uff0c\u662f\u7537\u5b69\u6c5f\u8fb9\u6e38\u73a9\u53d1\u73b0\uff01\u7f51\u53cb\uff1a\u4e0d\u53ef\u601d\u8bae|last1=Luo |first1=Xi (\u7f57\u5e0c) |last2=Liu |first2=Zhitang (\u5218\u5fd7\u68e0) |script-work=zh:\u6cb3\u6e90\u5e7f\u64ad\u7535\u89c6\u53f0 |trans-work=Heyuan Radio and TV |via=[[WeChat]] |access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n== Language ==\nIn the great majority of Heyuan areas, [[Hakka Chinese]] is in general use.\n\nIn the greater part of areas in the city, Dongyuan County, Lianping County, Heping County, Longchuan County etc., it belongs to the Yuezhong dialect group, while in Zijin County and part of Longchuan County, it belongs to the Yuetai dialect group.\n\nAlso, in some areas on the banks of the [[Dongjiang]], [[Dongjiang Bendihua]] is in general use. Its classification is disputed between the Yuezhong division of Hakka and the Huihe division of Yue.\n\n== Administration ==\n[[File:Txu-oclc-10552568-nf50-1.jpg|thumb|Map of Heyuan (labeled as HO-Y\u00dcAN (HOY\u00dcN) (Walled) {{lang|zh|\u6cb3\u6e90}}) and surrounding region ([[Army Map Service|AMS]], 1954)]]\nHeyuan City administers Yuancheng District, Dongyuan County, Heping County, Longchuan County, Zijin County and Lianping County. The total area is {{convert|15,800|km\u00b2}}. Heyuan city and its districts have a population of 3.2194 million. The municipality seat is in Yuancheng District.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n!colspan=\"6\"| Map\n! Name\n! Simplified Chinese\n! Hanyu Pinyin\n! Population<br/>{{nowrap|(2010 census)}}\n! Area<br/>(km<sup>2</sup>)\n! Density<br/>(/km<sup>2</sup>)\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"6\"| <div style=\"position: relative\" class=\"center\">\n{{Image label begin|image=Administrative Division Heyuan.png|width=450|link=}} \n{{Image label|x=170|y=620|scale=450/750|text=[[Xinfengjiang Reservoir|''Wanl\u00fc<br>Lake'']]}}\n{{Image label|x=160|y=680|scale=450/750|text=[[Yuancheng District|'''Yuancheng''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=400|y=740|scale=450/750|text=[[Zijin County|'''Zijin<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=600|y=300|scale=450/750|text=[[Longchuan County, Guangdong|'''Longchuan<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=110|y=250|scale=450/750|text=[[Lianping County|'''Lianping<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=400|y=230|scale=450/750|text=[[Heping County|'''Heping<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=280|y=510|scale=450/750|text=[[Dongyuan County|'''Dongyuan<br>County''']]}}\n</div>\n|[[Yuancheng District]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u6e90\u57ce\u533a}}\n|Yu\u00e1nch\u00e9ng Q\u016b\n|463,907\n|361.47\n|1,283\n|-\n|[[Zijin County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u7d2b\u91d1\u53bf}}\n|Z\u01d0j\u012bn Xi\u00e0n\n|640,133\n|3,635.13\n|225\n|-\n|[[Longchuan County, Guangdong|Longchuan County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u9f99\u5ddd\u53bf}}\n|L\u00f3ngchu\u0101n Xi\u00e0n\n|694,480\n|3,081.31\n|225\n|-\n|[[Lianping County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u8fde\u5e73\u53bf}}\n|Li\u00e1np\u00edng Xi\u00e0n\n|337,002\n|2,275.08\n|148\n|-\n|[[Heping County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u548c\u5e73\u53bf}}\n|H\u00e9p\u00edng Xi\u00e0n\n|374,709\n|2,291.45\n|164\n|-\n|[[Dongyuan County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u4e1c\u6e90\u53bf}}\n|D\u014dngyu\u00e1n Xi\u00e0n\n|439,964\n|4,009.17\n|110\n|}\n\n== Economy ==\nHeyuan city is a major economic and transportation hub for the Beijing-Kowloon Railway and the Guangzhou-Meizhou-Shantou Railway which crosses the city. There is also a marshalling station at Longchuan, which is the biggest in southern China.\n\nState Highway 105 and 205 run through the city.  Dong River which Heyuan City is located in plays an important strategic waterway which allows huge cargo ships to transport goods to Huizhou, Dongguan, and Guangzhou.\n\nHeyuan city is the major producer of Chinese kiwi fruit dried mushrooms of Jiulian, garlic, Hakka brewed liquor, Xinfengjiang pure water and mineral water, bamboo mats, sweet tangerines, green tea, and pot culture.\n\n== Transport ==\nHeyuan is served by the [[Hong Kong]]-[[Beijing]] [[Jingjiu railway]] with two stations: [[Heyuan railway station]] and [[Longchuan railway station]].\n\n== Attractions ==\n[[File:Heyuan Guifeng Ta 2015.11.12 12-28-46.jpg|thumbnail|Guifeng Pagoda]]\n\n=== Xinfengjiang Forest Park ===\n{{further|Xinfengjiang Reservoir}}\nHeyuan City has a number of tourist attractions. There is a tall fountain located in Xinfengjiang forest park. There are scenic areas such as the Dagui Mountain and the first big artificial lake; Wanlu Lake and the Sujiawei Round House.\n\n=== Longchuan County ===\nLongchuan county is home to scenic spots in Huoshan and Shuikeng.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n\n=== Lianping ===\nThe Neiguan Mountains and rivers are located in Lianping county.\n\n=== Dongyuan County ===\nIn Dongyuan county, there are scenic spots at Huanglong Crag and Zhangxi.\n\n== Sister cities ==\n{{unreferenced|section}}\n*{{flagdeco|Malaysia}} [[Kota Kinabalu]], Sabah, Malaysia\n*{{flagdeco|PRC}} [[Tieling]], [[Liaoning]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Heyuan}}\n* https://web.archive.org/web/20111103110304/http://www.heyuan.gov.cn/website/index.jsp {{in lang|zh}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120303155220/http://en.visitgd.com/overview/history/202877.shtml The history of Heyuan]\n\n{{Guangdong topics}}\n{{Guangdong}}\n{{Major cities along the Pearl River}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Prefecture-level divisions of Guangdong]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See Template:Infobox Settlement for additional fields that may be available-->\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|name                   = {{raise|0.2em|Heyuan}}\n|official_name          = <!-- Official name in English if different from 'name' -->\n|native_name            = {{lower|0.1em|{{nobold|{{lang|zh|\u6cb3\u6e90\u5e02}}}}}}\n|other_name             = \n|nickname               =\n|settlement_type        =[[Prefecture-level city]]\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  = \n<!-- images and maps  ----------